Project Overview
This project analyzes PizzaHut sales data using Microsoft SQL Server Management Studio. The analysis uncovers insights into sales trends, customer preferences, and business performance by addressing key business questions.

Features
Analyze sales trends and customer behaviors.
Discover top-performing pizza categories and sizes.
Gain insights into time-based ordering patterns.
Evaluate revenue contributions by pizza types and categories.

Datasets
The analysis uses four datasets to explore different aspects of PizzaHut’s sales performance.

Key Analyses
The project answers 13 critical business questions:

Retrieve the total number of orders placed.
Calculate total revenue from pizza sales.
Identify the highest-priced pizza.
Discover the most common pizza size ordered.
List the top 5 most-ordered pizza types with quantities.
Find the total quantity of pizzas ordered by category.
Analyze order distribution by hour of the day.
Explore category-wise pizza distribution.
Calculate the average number of pizzas ordered per day.
Identify the top 3 pizza types based on revenue.
Calculate each pizza type’s percentage contribution to total revenue.
Visualize cumulative revenue over time.
Analyze the top 3 pizza types by revenue in each category.

Tools Used
Microsoft SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS)
SQL for querying and analysis
Getting Started

Clone this repository.
Import the datasets into your SQL Server.
Use the provided SQL scripts to execute the analyses.
Contributions

Contributions to improve or expand the analysis are welcome. Please submit a pull request or open an issue.
